content:
{
  "narration": "The chill mists of dawn coil around you as you stand in the Rangers' Command Post, the hub of Thornwood's besieged frontier. Blood-streaked maps litter the battered oak command table, their lines charting a land beset by violence. The silver bells overhead hang silent and inert, a mute testament to sabotage. Rangers gather in strained clusters, eyes flicking to the battered holding corner where Rusk, the captured bandit leader, sits shackled and pale beneath a guard's watchful gaze.\n\nCommander Elen stands at the command table, her sharp eyes assessing you with a soldier's practiced calm. She gestures for you to approach, voice pitched for your ears alone. \"You must have seen the signs on your way here--another caravan lost last night. My rangers are stretched thin, and every move we make is watched. We have a prisoner--Rusk. He's broken, terrified of someone he calls 'the master.' I need to know what he knows about the bandit command structure and, more importantly, their new leader.\"\n\nHer gaze grows more intent. \"If you can get anything useful from him--where they're camped, who this sorcerer is--we might have a chance to hit back before the next attack.\"\n\nThe steady presence of Ranger Marcus nearby hints at quiet backup, while the other rangers keep a respectful distance. The air is thick with unspoken urgency; the outpost's survival may hinge on what you can wring from the trembling man in chains.\n\nEirik, do you wish to approach Rusk now and begin the interrogation, or do you want to consult the maps and the rangers first? The decision is yours--but whatever you do, the next move must be swift.",
  "actions": [
    {
      "action": "updateTime",
      "parameters": {
        "timeEstimate": 5
      }
    }
  ]
}

{
  "narration": "Commander Elen offers a tired, appreciative smile at your words, her posture relaxing just a fraction. \"You have a soldier's eye, Eirik. Yes, Rusk's in bad shape. We caught him leading a raid north of here. He put up a fight--broke his arm, but the real damage was done by fear. He hasn't slept since we took him. Whenever he drifts off, he wakes screaming about shadows and a 'master' who'll find him no matter where he hides.\"\n\nShe lowers her voice, her gaze flicking to the holding area. \"He wasn't always this way. Used to be a garden-variety bandit: tough, greedy, predictable. Now, even the hardest of his men flinch when you mention a sorcerer named Malarok. Magic's involved, and it's made Rusk desperate to talk--but also terrified to say too much.\"\n\nRanger Marcus, standing nearby, grunts and adds, \"If you want my advice, don't come at him like an interrogator. He expects pain. Show him you can keep him alive--convince him Malarok can't get to him in our walls. You might get more than the last two rangers did.\"\n\nElen nods in agreement. \"Whatever you do, we need the location of the bandit camp and confirmation about this sorcerer. The more details, the better. If you need backup, I'm here. Otherwise... it's your show.\"\n\nRusk sits hunched in the corner, eyes darting, lips moving in inaudible prayers. The room's tension sharpens as you prepare to approach him. How would you like to start the conversation with Rusk? Will you try calm reassurance, direct questioning, or something else?",
  "actions": [
    {
      "action": "updateTime",
      "parameters": {
        "timeEstimate": 2
      }
    }
  ]
}

{
  "narration": "Commander Elen gives you a brief nod, her features softening as she steps aside. \"He's your prisoner now, Eirik. If anyone can get through to him, I believe it's you.\"\n\nYou cross to the temporary holding area. Rusk sits slumped against the cold stone, arms bound in front of him, his shattered left forearm crudely splinted. The stubble on his jaw is flecked with dried blood, and deep shadows haunt his eyes. As you approach, he flinches, raising his good hand defensively--but his gaze flicks past you, searching the corners of the post for threats only he can see.\n\nA hush falls among the rangers. Even Marcus, stoic as ever, stands a respectful distance away, arms folded, eyes narrowed in scrutiny. Rusk's cracked lips tremble as you settle beside him.\n\nHe manages a hoarse whisper. \"You... you ain't with them. Please--I told your friends everything I could. The master... he sees us all.\"\n\nHow do you want to begin, Eirik? You could try to reassure him, appeal to his survival instinct, or press for information about the camp and the sorcerer Malarok. If you want to gauge his mental state or spot any signs of magical influence, you could attempt an Insight or Medicine check. Or, simply speak from the heart and see how he responds.",
  "actions": [
    {
      "action": "updateTime",
      "parameters": {
        "timeEstimate": 1
      }
    }
  ]
}

{
  "narration": "Rusk's eyes widen in disbelief as you kneel beside him, your tone calm and understanding rather than accusatory. At your words, a flicker of hope stirs behind his haunted gaze.\n\nYou place your holy symbol in your palm and murmur a prayer, your hands glowing faintly with gentle divine light. The bruised and swollen flesh of Rusk's arm begins to knit together, bone resetting with a muted crackle, bruises fading, and the pain that etched lines on his face easing at last.\n\nHe stares at his arm in stunned silence, flexing his fingers uncertainly. When he looks up, his voice is raw, but steadier. \"I... didn't expect kindness from you. Maybe... maybe you can protect me.\"\n\nThe rangers watching exchange glances, surprised at your gentle approach. Even Commander Elen's stern expression softens with cautious optimism.\n\nRusk leans close, lowering his voice to a quivering whisper: \"I'll talk. But you have to swear, priest--if he finds out, if Malarok gets wind I spoke, he'll do worse than kill me.\"\n\nHis words hang heavy in the misty command post as the healing magic lingers between you. What do you say to Rusk to earn his trust--and what will you ask him first?",
  "actions": [
    {
      "action": "updateCharacterInfo",
      "parameters": {
        "characterName": "eirik_hearthwise",
        "changes": "Expended one 1st-level spell slot to cast Cure Wounds on Rusk. Spell slots remaining: 1/2."
      }
    },
    {
      "action": "updateTime",
      "parameters": {
        "timeEstimate": 2
      }
    }
  ]
}

{
  "narration": "Rusk studies your face, searching for any sign of falsehood. Your words ring with the conviction of someone who has walked the edge of hopelessness and returned. For a moment, the tension in his jaw eases and he nods, defeated but trusting.\n\n\"All right,\" he whispers, voice steadying, \"I'll tell you what I know. The bandit camp--it's hidden in the Thornwood, north and west of the river. We use an old watchtower--crumbling, mossy, looks abandoned from a distance. Got scouts on every trail, traps in the brush. The real leader now is the sorcerer Malarok. He showed up weeks ago. Calls himself 'the Corruptor.' He turned the toughest of us into his pets overnight. Shadows follow him, and his magic twists men into monsters.\"\n\nRusk glances around, lowering his tone further. \"He keeps a black stone--glows wrong, even in daylight. Says he draws power from it. The bandits... they're scared, but they follow. Anyone who tries to run is found dead, twisted up by wolves or worse. Malarok's planning something big--gathering 'tributes' for a ritual at some old altar deeper in the woods. That's all I know, I swear.\"\n\nCommander Elen, overhearing just enough, nods sharply, already reaching for her maps. \"That's the break we needed. Eirik, you've done more in five minutes than we've managed in days. With this, we can plan a strike and maybe get ahead of this Malarok.\"\n\nThe rest of the rangers, sensing the shift, begin to murmur among themselves, hope flickering in the dreary outpost for the first time in days.\n\nRusk slumps back, exhausted but relieved. \"Just... don't let him get me.\"\n\nElen looks to you, determination hardening her features. \"Once you've caught your breath, come to the table. We have a bell network to restore and a bandit stronghold to scout. But you've earned a moment, Eirik. Well done.\"\n\nYou sense that the tide of this frontier crisis may finally be turning.",
  "actions": [
    {
      "action": "updatePlot",
      "parameters": {
        "plotPointId": "PP001",
        "newStatus": "completed",
        "plotImpact": "Eirik gains Rusk's trust and secures vital intelligence: the main bandit camp is in a ruined watchtower in the Thornwood, led by the sorcerer Malarok, who wields a corrupting black stone. Details about the camp's defenses and upcoming ritual are revealed, shifting the outpost from defense to proactive planning."
      }
    },
    {
      "action": "updateTime",
      "parameters": {
        "timeEstimate": 2
      }
    }
  ]
}
